Author: Mohamed Tawfiq Cassim
README File
ASP.NET Core | C# | SQL Server | Entity Framework Core

Overview
This ASP.NET Core MVC web application was developed as a Software Engineering technical assessment for an IoT hardware company. The system manages 
varying tracking and monitoring devices, firmware versions, and hierarchical device groups. Built using a Database First approach with Entity Framework Core,
it connects to a relational SQL Server database. The solution highlights clean architecture and effective database management following the standard MVC pattern.

Features
- Dashboard (Total Devices, Firmware Versions, Device Groups, Device Types)
- Firmware Management (View firmware versions, Add new firmware, Edit existing firmware, Delete firmware)
- Group Management (Create and manage hierarchical device groups, Edit group information, Delete groups)
- Device Management (Read-only view of registered IoT devices, Displays associated Device Type, Firmware Version, and Group)

Database Design
The database was designed using Microsoft SQL Server and follows relational database principles.
Tables - DeviceTypes, Firmware, Groups, Devices
Relationships:
- One Device Type can have many Devices.
- One Firmware version can be installed on many Devices.
- One Group can contain many Devices.
- Groups support hierarchical parent-child relationships through a self-referencing foreign key.

